
<p>'Tis whiter than an Indian Pipe —<br>
'Tis dimmer than a Lace —<br>
No stature has it, like a Fog<br>
When you approach the place —<br>
Nor any voice imply it here<br>
Or intimate it there<br>
A spirit — how doth it accost —<br>
What function hath the Air?<br>
This limitless Hyperbole<br>
Each one of us shall be —<br>
'Tis Drama — if Hypothesis<br>
It be not Tragedy —</p>
